content.description: Ok problem with good rock. An obvious line of holds angling across the face. Sit start on the left side of the face at the crack, moving up to a good left hand. Follow the good rails to a good topout. Downclimb the same problem.
content.protection: Pad. Spotter will help with the downclimb if you weren't super solid on the send.

content.description: Another ok line. Squat start on right arete in some questionable rock. Move up the arete to a good quartz jug, then left to join the main line of holds to the top. Downclimb the face.
content.protection: Pad, the landing starts to slope away so mind your ankles if you come off.
content.location: Right arete of uphill face. Downclimb route to left.

content.description: This boulder is visible from the parking pullout. Look uphill and a little left to spot a formation with two diagonal quartz bands.   The uphill side has two easy problems with good rock, while the other faces are much taller with questionable landings.
